						               													<description>In Cockroach Salad players create a common salad packed with lettuce, peppers, tomatoes and cauliflower &amp;ndash; but they won't always be saying which ingredient they're adding to the bowl!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 128 cards &amp;ndash; 120 vegetable cards in the four types and eight &amp;quot;taboo&amp;quot; vegetable cards, two of each type that bear cockroaches &amp;ndash; are shuffled and divided among the players. On a turn, a player plays the top card from his deck onto the central pile of cards, naming the vegetable as he plays it, e.g., &amp;quot;Pepper!&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; except in the following situations:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; If his vegetable matches the previously played vegetable, the player must lie.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; If his vegetable matches the claim made by the previous player (perhaps because that player lied), then the player must lie.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; If he plays a taboo card, he shouts &amp;quot;Cockroach!&amp;quot; and the next player starts a new pile next to the first one so that the taboo card remains visible.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; If his vegetable matches a visible taboo card, he must lie.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Make a mistake or stumble or hesitate too long, and a player must pick up all cards played to that point in the game. The first player to run out of cards wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Can be combined with Kakerlakensuppe.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
